    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter today\u2019s slate with **Yordan Alvarez** leading the charge, posting an elite 82.97 efficiency score. His favorable matchup against Gil (5.74 xERA) combined with a prime #2 spot in the order makes him our cornerstone asset. **Junior Caminero** follows as our secondary anchor at 71.00; he benefits significantly from Woods Richardson\u2019s high xERA and a positive platoon adjustment. While **Trea Turner** and **Kyle Schwarber** draw a tough assignment against Sale, their inherent talent and leadoff/high-order utility keep them firmly in the starting rotation, though owners should anticipate tempered expectations against such a high-caliber arm. \n\nStrategic lineup construction today heavily favors high-upside matchups despite some volatility in the bottom third. **Luke Raley** remains a high-value start at 57.91, capitalizing on a weak opponent starter (McGreevy), while **Victor Scott II** continues to be our primary weapon in the scarce stolen base category, despite an unfavorable #9 order slot and Hancock\u2019s efficiency at holding runners. **Caleb Durbin** also remains active, buoyed by a substantial 16% park factor bump that helps mitigate the challenge posed by Bradish. The closest bench decision involved **Chase Meidroth**; despite a positive platoon advantage and a leadoff projection, his 44.54 score fell just short of our threshold for displacing our existing starters, as the optimizer prioritized the specific positional scarcity and higher raw ceiling of our current utility options. \n\nWe are monitoring the **Hyeseong Kim** situation closely, as his status remains \"Lineup Pending.\" While his base projection is solid, the combination of a difficult matchup against Imanaga and a L/L platoon disadvantage adds significant risk to his 48.31 score. Furthermore, we are exercising caution with **Gary Sanchez**, **Josh Smith**, **Colt Keith**, and **Kazuma Okamoto**; all are in the \"Marginal\" range (40\u201359), requiring disciplined monitoring to ensure they don't drift into our \"Below floor\" category if official lineups shift unfavorably. Aside from **Zac Veen**, who remains in the minors, the rest of our depth\u2014including **Christian Yelich**, **Lars Nootbaar**, **Jerar Encarnacion**, **Dillon Dingler**, **Pete Crow-Armstrong**, **Carson Benge**, and **Luis Pena**\u2014remains ready to rotate in should late-scratch reports impact our starters.",
